Institution: use the darwin core standard (http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/index.htm) to "crosswalk" these data describing fungi specimens. Basically, the headers for each of these columns are now in human-speak or what a researcher might record. Change them to darwin core terms so that they can be uploaded into a database or aggregator alongside other similar data. The act of matching column headers to their appropriate term within a standard is called crosswalking and is a common step in the upload/publication of datasets.
